  "texts": [
    "Provided that other technologies (even non-AI ones) are potentially related to many of the hazards involved in the use of LLMs, LLMs stand out in that they qualify as multi-hazard systems.",
    "So, not only the large-scale use of LLM-based applications is unprecedented, which makes these technologies experimental in van de Poel's (2016) sense.",
    "It is also characterised by high degrees of flexibility, for LLMs can easily be fine-tuned to specific tasks that need not be anticipated by the initial designers.",
    "These two features of LLMs make it extremely difficult to predict ex-ante the risks involved in the use of such technologies, for the operational experience with them is limited and it is hard to anticipate all their possible applications, and therefore all the associated risks.",
    "Sure, ex-post analyses can be performed after the occurrence of unwanted events related to the use of LLMs."
  ],
